  15 @contextlib.contextmanager
  16 def tempdir():
  17     tmpdir = tempfile.mkdtemp()
  18     try:
  19         yield pathlib.Path(tmpdir)
  20     finally:
  21         shutil.rmtree(tmpdir)
  22 
  23 
  24 @contextlib.contextmanager
  25 def save_cwd():
  26     orig = os.getcwd()
  27     try:
  28         yield
  29     finally:
  30         os.chdir(orig)
  31 
  32 
  33 @contextlib.contextmanager
  34 def tempdir_as_cwd():
  35     with tempdir() as tmp:
  36         with save_cwd():
  37             os.chdir(str(tmp))
  38             yield tmp
  39 
  40 
  41 @contextlib.contextmanager
  42 def install_finder(finder):
  43     sys.meta_path.append(finder)
  44     try:
  45         yield
  46     finally:
  47         sys.meta_path.remove(finder)

  50 class Fixtures:
  51     def setUp(self):
  52         self.fixtures = contextlib.ExitStack()
  53         self.addCleanup(self.fixtures.close)
  54 
  55 
  56 class SiteDir(Fixtures):
  57     def setUp(self):
  58         super(SiteDir, self).setUp()
  59         self.site_dir = self.fixtures.enter_context(tempdir())

  61 
  62 class OnSysPath(Fixtures):
  63     @staticmethod
  64     @contextlib.contextmanager
  65     def add_sys_path(dir):
  66         sys.path[:0] = [str(dir)]
  67         try:
  68             yield
  69         finally:
  70             sys.path.remove(str(dir))
  71 
  72     def setUp(self):
  73         super(OnSysPath, self).setUp()
  74         self.fixtures.enter_context(self.add_sys_path(self.site_dir))

 169 def build_files(file_defs, prefix=pathlib.Path()):
 170     """Build a set of files/directories, as described by the
 171 
 172     file_defs dictionary.  Each key/value pair in the dictionary is
 173     interpreted as a filename/contents pair.  If the contents value is a
 174     dictionary, a directory is created, and the dictionary interpreted
 175     as the files within it, recursively.
 176 
 177     For example:
 178 
 179     {"README.txt": "A README file",
 180      "foo": {
 181         "__init__.py": "",
 182         "bar": {
 183             "__init__.py": "",
 184         },
 185         "baz.py": "# Some code",
 186      }
 187     }
 188     """
 189     for name, contents in file_defs.items():
 190         full_name = prefix / name
 191         if isinstance(contents, dict):
 192             full_name.mkdir()
 193             build_files(contents, prefix=full_name)
 194         else:
 195             if isinstance(contents, bytes):
 196                 with full_name.open('wb') as f:
 197                     f.write(contents)
 198             else:
 199                 with full_name.open('w') as f:
 200                     f.write(DALS(contents))
 201 
 202 
 203 def DALS(str):
 204     "Dedent and left-strip"
 205     return textwrap.dedent(str).lstrip()
